The paper deals with the problem of recognition in new unseen domains, which is a common problem in computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) applications. The proposed method is based on deep learning techniques, which are widely used in CV and ML research. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses domain adaptation, feature transferring, and fine-tuning, which are related to machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG and cs.AI). The proposed method involves the use of deep neural networks, which are a type of neural network (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on different datasets, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM).
